         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper, a class of complex harmonic spline functions (C.H.S.) are defined on the unit disc $U$. We use the C.H.S. to approximate the complex harmonic function on $U$, showing that C.H.S. may be represented by elementary functions. If the maximum step tends to zero and the mesh ratio is bounded, then C.H.S. converge uniformly to the interpolated function $F$ on the closed disc $\bar U$. If the interpolated function $F$ is a conformal mapping, then the C.H.S. is a quasi-conformal mapping.</p>
          </abstract>
